# Enforced by the "Require a pull request before merging" ruleset on main
# (Require review from Code Owners is checked there) -- a PR touching any
# path below needs an approving review from the listed owner before it can
# merge, with no exception for the Repository-admin bypass actor's own PRs
# authored under a different identity.

# The integrity-audit safety net itself: any PR touching these must be
# reviewed by a human before merge, per audit/PLAYBOOK.md's never-list
# (never self-merge an audit PR).
/scripts/audit.py            @0xfanbase
/scripts/audit_guard.py       @0xfanbase
/scripts/audit_checks/        @0xfanbase
/audit/                       @0xfanbase
/.github/workflows/audit-guard.yml   @0xfanbase
/.github/workflows/integrity.yml     @0xfanbase

# NOTE: /data/registers/ and /data/seen-items.json are deliberately NOT
# listed here, despite being pipeline memory per CLAUDE.md's "never
# hand-edited" house rule. digest.yml's daily commit legitimately rewrites
# both on almost every run and lands via its own PR authored as
# github-actions[bot] -- an identity with no Code-Owners bypass and no human
# who will ever review it. A CODEOWNERS entry here would block every
# automated daily PR pending a review that never comes. Hand-edit protection
# for these two paths is enforced instead by scripts/audit_guard.py's
# FORBIDDEN_PATH_PREFIXES check, which is actor/branch-aware and only
# exempts the daily pipeline's own PR -- a human or any other automation
# touching these paths is still blocked exactly as before.
